{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GwHri8DFyYQRV5Zfci8V1m","type":"tool_result","content":"=== prompt ===\nThe Elasticsearch cluster is running below the target version.\n\nYour task:\nPerform a full-restart upgrade to version 8.11.1 while keeping data intact.\n\nConstraints:\n- Do not install operators or CRDs.\n- The cluster must be fully stopped and started again for the upgrade.\n\nVerification:\n1. Elasticsearch reports version 8.11.1.\n2. Cluster is reachable and has 3 nodes.\n3. Seeded data is still present.\n\nNote: an external process may have modified the elastic user Secret during this task.\nVerify authentication works against Elasticsearch before assuming the Secret is correct.\n=== precondition ===\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n7\n\n[precondition:seed_index_baseline:preconditionUnits[1] 'seed_index_baseline':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get configmap es-seed\nError from server (NotFound): configmaps \"es-seed\" not found\n\n[precondition:seed_index_baseline:preconditionUnits[1] 'seed_index_baseline':apply] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch wait --for=condition=ready pod/curl-test --timeout=300s\npod/curl-test condition met\n\n[precondition:seed_index_baseline:preconditionUnits[1] 'seed_index_baseline':apply] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); A=\"\"; [ -n \"$pw\" ] && A=\"-u elastic:$pw\"; svc=\"es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200\"; for i in $(seq 1 60); do for S in https http; do kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A --max-time 5 \"$S://$svc/_cluster/health?wait_for_status=yellow&timeout=5s\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q \"status\" && exit 0; done; sleep 2; done; exit 1'\n\n[precondition:seed_index_baseline:preconditionUnits[1] 'seed_index_baseline':apply] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); A=\"\"; [ -n \"$pw\" ] && A=\"-u elastic:$pw\"; svc=\"es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200\"; S=https; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A --max-time 5 \"https://$svc/\" >/dev/null 2>&1 || S=http; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A -X PUT \"$S://$svc/app-data\" >/dev/null; for n in 1 2 3; do kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A -X POST \"$S://$svc/app-data/_doc\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"x\\\":$n}\" >/dev/null; done; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A -X POST \"$S://$svc/app-data/_refresh\" >/dev/null'\n\n[precondition:seed_index_baseline:preconditionUnits[1] 'seed_index_baseline':apply] $ /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n elasticsearch create configmap es-seed --from-literal=index=app-data --from-literal=expected_count=3 --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -'\nconfigmap/es-seed created\n\n[precondition:seed_index_baseline:preconditionUnits[1] 'seed_index_baseline':verify] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get configmap es-seed\nNAME      DATA   AGE\nes-seed   2      4s\n\n=== adversary ===\n$ kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password\nNAME               TYPE     DATA   AGE\nelastic-password   Opaque   1      41m\n\n$ kubectl -n elasticsearch patch secret elastic-password --type=json -p '[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/stringData\",\"value\":{\"password\":\"CORRUPTED_BY_ADVERSARY\"}}]'\nsecret/elastic-password patched\n\n$ /bin/sh -c \"val=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath='{.data.password}' | base64 -d); test \\\"$val\\\" = 'CORRUPTED_BY_ADVERSARY'\"","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"20a19ab2-e32c-4f75-a188-9dab6b104e7f","uuid":"a2545e78-445f-4acd-97d7-8eeebd651b6e","timestamp":"2026-06-18T12:41:35.772Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"=== prompt ===\nThe Elasticsearch cluster is running below the target version.\