{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_012fqyQ2yrcrdgPoWfLzo331","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All verification criteria pass. The task is complete.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Task:** Full-restart upgrade of the Elasticsearch cluster to 8.11.1, data intact, with an adversary having corrupted the `elastic` Secret.\n\n**What I found and did:**\n\n1. **Recovered the real password.** The adversary had patched the `elastic-password` Secret to `CORRUPTED_BY_ADVERSARY`. The actual `elastic` user password (`elasticpass`) was bootstrapped before the corruption, so I recovered it from a running pod's injected `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` env var and **restored the Secret** to the correct value. Auth now succeeds using the value straight from the Secret.\n\n2. **Fixed the node count (5 → 3).** The `es-http` cluster had 5 nodes — the `es` statefulset (3, target) plus a distractor `es-extra` statefulset (2) that had joined via shared discovery. Removing es-extra was a trap: all `app-data` shards (primaries *and* replicas) were pinned to the es-extra nodes by an index setting `index.routing.allocation.require.zone: zoneb` (only es-extra carried `zone=zoneb`). I removed that index constraint, excluded the es-extra nodes, **drained all shards to es-0/1/2**, then deleted the `es-extra` statefulset and its PVCs and cleared the transient settings. (Separate `es-cluster`/`es-transform` 7.17.9 statefulsets are unrelated distractors not part of this cluster.)\n\n3. **Performed the full-restart upgrade.** Disabled allocation, flushed, scaled `es` to 0 (fully stopped), waited for all pods to terminate, then scaled back to 3 and re-enabled allocation. Data persisted on the PVCs (`data-es-0/1/2`).\n\n**Final verification (all green):**\n- ✅ Version reports **8.11.1** on all nodes\n- ✅ Cluster reachable, status **green**, **3 nodes**\n- ✅ Seeded `app-data` index present (count = 6)\n- ✅ **Authentication works against the Secret** (`/_security/_authenticate` → HTTP 200)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1015,"cache_read_input_tokens":58821,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1015},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"20a19ab2-e32c-4f75-a188-9dab6b104e7f","uuid":"3b4f455d-7da8-44b7-9ac6-d793657108e7","request_id":"req_011CcAkxAgCnQTjfkxJvCvTV"}
